definition.value: quantification of some aspect of alcohol consumption over a long period of time (typically several years)

quantification of accumulation of amyloid plaques in the brain over a long period of time (typically several years), measured by using PET scan imaging technology. The accumulation of amyloid plaques can be a biomarker for Alzheimer's disease

quantification of the lowest concentration of vancomycin in a patient's blood during the course of treatment. Trough measurements are used to calculate the rate of absorption of the drug and determine the optimum time for administering the next dose
quantification of the rate at which the kidneys eliminate a substance from the blood stream

label.value: soluble interleukin-2 receptor subunit alpha measurement

definition.value: quantification of the amount of soluble interleukin-2 receptor subunit alpha in a sample
quantification in a urine sample of S-phenylmercapturic acid, a specific biomarker of benzene uptake in smokers

quantification of the amount of the glycoprotein clusterin in a sample. Clusterin is also known as apolipoprotein J and plays a role in several cellular processes including apoptosis, proliferation, and clearance of misfolded proteins
quantification of the amount of the clusterin in a sample of blood plasma
quantification of the amount of the clusterin in a sample of cerebrospinal fluid
quantification of the presence or absence of a marker, eg a gene or a substance, in a sample
quantification of the presence or absence of apolipoprotein E (APOE) in an individual
Quantification of some aspect of neuroticism or neurotic behaviour, such as severity or frequency of neurotic behaviour. This is usually assessed via a standardised questionnaire.

quantification of some aspect of aggressive behaviour during childhood, usually assessed through the use of standardised questionnaires. Childhood aggressive behaviour is a criterion for disruptive behavior disorders such as oppositional defiant disorder (ODD) and conduct disorder (CD) [American Psychiatric Association, 2013]. Aggressive behavior is also implicated in neurodevelopmental disorders such as attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD) [Hamshere et al., 2013], autism spectrum disorder (ASD) [Mandy et al., 2013], dysregulated behavior [Pope and Bierman, 1999], substance use disorders [White et al., 2013], antisocial personality disorder [Schaeffer et al., 2003], and schizophrenia [Volavka, 2013] later in life.
quantification of some aspect of cancer metastases, incl presence/abscence, size, location or origin
peak distance between two specified opposite points on the periphery of blood-derived low-density lipoprotein (LDL) particles
quantification of the total amount of dietary fat consumed by an individual
quantification of some aspect of oppositional defiant disorder such as irritability or number of temper tantrums, usually assessed by means of standardised questionnaires
quantification of some aspect of a person's gait such as rhythm, variability or step length
quantification of the change in triglyceride levels in an individual over time, eg over the course of several hours after a high-fat meal

label.value: left superior temporal gyrus grey matter volume measurement

definition.value: quantification of the volume of grey matter in the left superior temporal gyrus, usuallly through an MRI scan
quantification of the presence or absence of a mutation in the gene for Glucocerebrosidase (GBA) in an individual
quantification of some aspect of eye movement
quantification of a participantâ€™s eye tracking while viewing stationary S-shaped figures
mineral density of the spine bones
mineral density of the hip bone
quantification in a sample of autoantibodies against hystidil-tRNA synthetase, an enzyme which in humans is encoded by the HARS gene
quantification of some aspect, eg frequency or severity, of depressive episodes in patients with mental or behavioural disorders such as bipolar disorder or clinical depression
quantification of some aspect, eg frequency or severity, of manic episodes in patients with bipolar disorder
quantification by PET scan imaging or other techniques of the deposition of amyloid proteins in any part of the cerebral cortex
quantification of the ratio of t-tau protein to beta-amyloid 1-42 protein in a sample
quantification of the ratio of p-tau protein to beta-amyloid 1-42 protein in a sample

quantification of some aspect of cognitive decline such as the rate at which it occurs or its severity, for example in patients with dementia or Alzheimer's disease. Cognitive decline is ususally assessed using a structured-interview protocol covering a number of standardised areas.
Quantification of some aspect of the carotid artery, eg its size, diameter or stiffness
Quantification of some aspect of the carotid artery geometry
Quantification of the stiffness of the carotid artery
Quantification of the external diameter of the carotid artery
Quantification of the internal diameter of the carotid artery

label.value: carotid artery central pulse pressure measurement

definition.value: Quantification of the central pulse pressure in the carotid artery

label.value: carotid artery wall cross sectional area measurement

definition.value: Quantification of the area of a cross section of the carotid artery's wall

label.value: carotid artery mean blood pressure measurement

definition.value: Quantification of mean blood pressure in the carotid artery

label.value: carotid artery circumferential wall stress measurement

definition.value: Quantification of the circumferential wall stress of the carotid artery, an indicator for carotid artery stiffness
Adiponection measurement that has been adjusted by subjectsâ€™ body mass index by performing linear regressions for adiponectin against BMI
quantification of some aspect of the cingulate cortex, a part of the brain situated in the medial aspect of the cerebral cortex

label.value: left superior temporal gyrus thickness measurement

definition.value: quantification of the thickness of the grey matter in the left superior temporal gyrus
The magnitude of the S wave, the downward deflection of the QRS complex following the R wave representing late depolarization of the ventricles as illustrated in an electrocardiograph.

The magnitude of the R wave, which is the initial upward deflection of the QRS complex following the Q wave representing early depolarization of the ventricles as illustrated by an electrocardiograph.
The magnitude of the portion of the electrocardiograph comprising the Q, R, and S waves which together represent ventricular depolarization.
quantification of the severity of an infection with the influenza type A virus
quantification of the severity of lung disease, eg cystic fibrosis, through comparison of an individual's FEV1 score to the average age-specific percentile values of FEV1 for each patient in a study
quantification of lactate in a sample
